descript.abstract: Regional Offices manage, operate and maintain all delegated programs, functions and activities not managed, operated or maintained by headquarters organizational units....the FEMA Regional Offices serve as the primary organizational unit for liaison to states and local governments within each region, and non-governmental and private sector entities within each Regional Office's geographical area
descript.purpose: To establish a Regional, all-hazards emergency management system of preparedness, mitigation, response and recovery, through close working relationships with Federal agencies, State and local governments, business and industry, and volunteer organizations, in implementing FEMA policies.
